TAMPA — Preparations are underway in Nashville as the NHL transforms Nissan Stadium, home of the NFL’s Tennessee Titans, for Saturday’s Stadium Series game between the Lightning and Predators. It will be the first outdoor game in Lightning history. They will become the 27th of the league’s 32 teams to participate in an outdoor game. Here are some notable numbers about outdoor games. 4 Times in which a goaltender has recorded a shutout in an outdoor game: Calgary’s Miikka Kiprusoff (2011 Heritage Classic), Anaheim’s Jonas Hiller (2014 Stadium Series), Edmonton’s Cam Talbot (2016 Heritage Classic) and Ottawa’s Craig Anderson (NHL100 Classic). Lightning goaltender Andrei Vasilevskiy has 28 career shutouts, including one in 11 games against Nashville. 7 Number of outdoor games that have required overtime to be decided. Five ended in the overtime session, two in shootouts. 16 Penalty minutes accrued by Lightning forward Corey Perry in his two outdoor games, second-most behind Michal Rozsival’s 17. While playing for Dallas in 2019-20, Perry was ejected from the Winter Classic at the Cotton Bowl for elbowing Predators defenseman Ryan Ellis just 2:44 into the game. 18 Number of Stanley Cup winners on the Lightning roster, which is tied for second-most on one team to participate in an outdoor game. The 2013-14 Blackhawks had 19 Cup winners in their Stadium Series game at Soldier Field. The 2008-09 Red Wings (Winter Classic at Wrigley Field) and 2014-15 Blackhawks (Winter Classic at Nationals Park) each had 18 Cup winners on their rosters. 20 Number of outdoor games, including Saturday’s, that have been held in football stadiums. Eleven took place in baseball stadiums, two on golf courses and one in a soccer stadium. 50 The average high temperature for Nashville on Feb. 26 (the date of this year’s Stadium Series game), according to accuweather.com (in degrees Fahrenheit). 165 Seconds into the game in which Corey Perry opened the scoring in the 2014 Stadium Series game at Dodger Stadium. Then playing for Anaheim, Perry scored at 2:45,  the fifth-fastest goal to start an NHL outdoor game. .606 Points percentage of road teams in outdoor games. Road teams are 18-11-4 in such games. 53,571 Average attendance at the 33 previous outdoor games (not counting games that couldn’t be attended). The largest crowd the Lightning have played in front of this season is 19,976 on Dec. 7 in a 3-2 win at Bell Centre in Montreal. The capacity of Nissan Stadium is 69,143. • • • The Tampa Bay Times has commemorated the Lightning’s second consecutive Stanley Cup title with a new hardcover coffee table book, Striking Twice. Order now. Sign up for Lightning Strikes, a weekly newsletter from Bolts beat writer Eduardo A. Encina that brings you closer to the ice. Never miss out on the latest with the Bucs, Rays, Lightning, Florida college sports and more. Follow our Tampa Bay Times sports team on Twitter and Facebook.